==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pseudo-symmetry
<hw>Pseu`do-sym"me*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pseudo-</ets> + <ets>symmetry</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>A kind of symmetry characteristic of
certain crystals which from twinning, or other causes, come to resemble
forms of a system other than that to which they belong, as the
apparently hexagonal prisms of aragonite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pseudotetramera</ent>⟦br⟧
